    "---\n",
    "## 15. Mean Reversion Strategien\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theorie\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mean Reversion** (Regression zum Mittelwert) beschreibt die Tendenz von Preisen oder Spreads, nach Abweichungen von ihrem historischen Mittelwert dorthin zurückzukehren.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mathematisches Fundament – Ornstein-Uhlenbeck Prozess:**\n",
    "$$dX_t = \\kappa (\\theta - X_t) dt + \\sigma dW_t$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- $\\kappa$: **Mean-Reversion-Geschwindigkeit** (wie schnell kehrt X zu θ zurück?). Halbwertszeit: $t_{1/2} = \\ln(2)/\\kappa$\n",
    "- $\\theta$: Langfristiger Mittelwert\n",
    "- $\\sigma$: Volatilität der Störterme\n",
    "\n",
    "### Wann funktioniert Mean Reversion?\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Spreads** zwischen verwandten Assets (Pairs Trading)\n",
    "- **Devisenpaare** (Kaufkraftparität als langfristiger Anker)\n",
    "- **Zinsstruktur** (Short Rates revertieren zum langfristigen Gleichgewicht)\n",
    "- **Volatilität** (VIX revertiert zu historischem Mittelwert ~20)\n",
    "- **Aktien** auf kurzen Zeitrahmen (1–5 Tage) oft Mean-Reverting\n",
    "\n",
    "### Warnsignale\n",
    "\n",
    "**Nicht verwechseln mit Random Walk:** Die meisten Preiszeitreihen sind einzeln **keine** Mean-Reverting Prozesse. Mean Reversion zeigt sich typisch in **Preisdifferenzen** oder **relativen Bewertungen** (z.B. KGV), nicht in absoluten Preisen.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quelle:** Chan (2013), Kap. 2; Avellaneda, M. & Lee, J. (2010). *Statistical Arbitrage in the US Equities Market*. Quantitative Finance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Ornstein-Uhlenbeck Simulation ────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "def simulate_ou(kappa, theta, sigma, x0, T, dt=1/TRADING_DAYS):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Simulates an Ornstein-Uhlenbeck process.\"\"\"\n",
    "    n    = int(T / dt)\n",
    "    x    = np.zeros(n)\n",
    "    x[0] = x0\n",
    "    for t in range(1, n):\n",
    "        dW   = np.random.normal(0, np.sqrt(dt))\n",
    "        x[t] = x[t-1] + kappa * (theta - x[t-1]) * dt + sigma * dW\n",
    "    return x\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vergleich: starke vs. schwache Mean Reversion\n",
    "kappa_fast = 50.0   # Halbwertszeit: ln(2)/50 ≈ 5 Handelstage\n",
    "kappa_slow = 5.0    # Halbwertszeit: ln(2)/5  ≈ 35 Handelstage\n",
    "T_ou = 2.0          # 2 Jahre\n",
    "\n",
    "ou_fast = simulate_ou(kappa_fast, 0, 0.05, 0.1, T_ou)\n",
    "ou_slow = simulate_ou(kappa_slow, 0, 0.05, 0.1, T_ou)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Einfache Bollinger-Band Mean-Reversion Strategie ─────────────────────────\n",
    "spread = pd.Series(ou_fast)\n",
    "roll_mean = spread.rolling(20).mean()\n",
    "roll_std  = spread.rolling(20).std()\n",
    "upper     = roll_mean + 1.5 * roll_std\n",
    "lower     = roll_mean - 1.5 * roll_std\n",
    "\n",
    "# Signal: -1 wenn spread > upper (short), +1 wenn spread < lower (long)\n",
    "signal    = np.where(spread > upper, -1, np.where(spread < lower, 1, 0))\n",
    "signal    = pd.Series(signal).shift(1).fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Halbwertszeit (Fast κ={kappa_fast}): {np.log(2)/kappa_fast*TRADING_DAYS:.1f} Handelstage')\n",
    "print(f'Halbwertszeit (Slow κ={kappa_slow}): {np.log(2)/kappa_slow*TRADING_DAYS:.1f} Handelstage')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(13, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "# OU Prozesse\n",
    "axes[0].plot(ou_fast, color='#e74c3c', lw=1, label=f'Fast κ={kappa_fast} (HWZ={np.log(2)/kappa_fast*TRADING_DAYS:.0f}d)')\n",
    "axes[0].plot(ou_slow, color='#3498db', lw=1.5, label=f'Slow κ={kappa_slow} (HWZ={np.log(2)/kappa_slow*TRADING_DAYS:.0f}d)')\n",
    "axes[0].axhline(0, color='black', lw=1, ls='--', label='Langfristiger Mittelwert θ=0')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Ornstein-Uhlenbeck Prozess: Vergleich Reversion-Geschwindigkeit', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bollinger Band Strategie\n",
    "axes[1].plot(spread.values, color='#4a90d9', lw=1, label='Spread')\n",
    "axes[1].plot(roll_mean.values, color='black', lw=1.5, ls='--', label='Rolling Mean')\n",
    "axes[1].plot(upper.values, color='#e74c3c', lw=1, ls=':', label='+1.5σ (Short Signal)')\n",
    "axes[1].plot(lower.values, color='#2ecc71', lw=1, ls=':', label='-1.5σ (Long Signal)')\n",
    "buy_idx  = np.where(signal == 1)[0]\n",
    "sell_idx = np.where(signal == -1)[0]\n",
    "axes[1].scatter(buy_idx,  spread.iloc[buy_idx],  color='#2ecc71', s=30, zorder=5, label='Long')\n",
    "axes[1].scatter(sell_idx, spread.iloc[sell_idx], color='#e74c3c', s=30, zorder=5, label='Short')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Bollinger-Band Mean-Reversion Strategie', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('mean_reversion.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
