    "---\n",
    "## 16. Momentum und Trend Following\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theorie\n",
    "\n",
    "**Momentum** beschreibt die empirisch beobachtete Tendenz: **Assets die in der Vergangenheit gut performt haben, tendieren dazu, kurzfristig weiter gut zu performen.** Das ist das Gegenteil von Mean Reversion.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Jegadeesh & Titman (1993):** Der bekannteste Nachweis: Aktien-Gewinner der letzten 3–12 Monate outperformen in den nächsten 3–12 Monaten. Momentum-Prämie ~7–10% p.a. historisch, aber sehr krisenanfällig (\"Momentum Crashes\").\n",
    "\n",
    "### Formen von Momentum\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Cross-Sectional Momentum (CS-Mom):** Kaufe die besten 20% der Aktien, verkaufe die schlechtesten 20%. Relativ zwischen Assets.\n",
    "- **Time-Series Momentum (TS-Mom):** Kaufe wenn ein Asset über seinem historischen Mittelwert liegt, egal wie es relativ zu anderen performt. Auch: **Trend Following**.\n",
    "- **Dual Momentum (Antonacci):** Kombiniere CS-Mom und TS-Mom.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Technische Indikatoren für Trend Following\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Moving Average Crossover:** Wenn kurzfristiger MA (z.B. 50 Tage) über langfristigen MA (200 Tage) kreuzt → Kaufsignal (\"Golden Cross\")\n",
    "- **MACD (Moving Average Convergence Divergence)**\n",
    "- **Breakout-Systeme:** Kaufe wenn Preis neues 52-Wochen-Hoch erreicht\n",
    "\n",
    "### Warum funktioniert Momentum?\n",
    "\n",
    "Behavioral Finance: **Underreaction** zu Unternehmensnachrichten (Investoren passen ihre Erwartungen zu langsam an) und **Herding** (Investoren folgen Trends). Kein Free Lunch – Momentum Strategien erfahren periodisch extreme Verluste (\"Momentum Crashes\") wenn Trends abrupt enden.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quelle:** Jegadeesh & Titman (1993); Moskowitz, T. et al. (2012). *Time Series Momentum*. Journal of Financial Economics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Moving Average Crossover Strategie ───────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "T_mom = 1260   # 5 Jahre\n",
    "# Simuliere Preisserie mit leichtem Trend und Clustering\n",
    "drift   = 0.0003\n",
    "returns_m = np.zeros(T_mom)\n",
    "vol_now   = 0.012\n",
    "for t in range(T_mom):\n",
    "    # GARCH-ähnliche Volatilität\n",
    "    vol_now   = np.sqrt(0.00003 + 0.1 * (returns_m[t-1]**2 if t>0 else 0.0001) + 0.85 * vol_now**2)\n",
    "    returns_m[t] = drift + vol_now * np.random.randn()\n",
    "\n",
    "prices_m = pd.Series(100 * np.exp(np.cumsum(returns_m)))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Moving Averages\n",
    "ma_50  = prices_m.rolling(50).mean()\n",
    "ma_200 = prices_m.rolling(200).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Signal: Long wenn MA50 > MA200\n",
    "signal_ma = (ma_50 > ma_200).astype(int).shift(1).fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strategie-Renditen\n",
    "ret_m   = prices_m.pct_change().fillna(0)\n",
    "strat_r = signal_ma * ret_m\n",
    "\n",
    "cum_bh   = (1 + ret_m).cumprod()\n",
    "cum_strat = (1 + strat_r).cumprod()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Performance\n",
    "def perf(r, label):\n",
    "    cum = (1+r).cumprod()\n",
    "    cagr= cum.iloc[-1]**(TRADING_DAYS/T_mom) - 1\n",
    "    vol = r.std() * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS)\n",
    "    sr  = (cagr - RISK_FREE) / vol\n",
    "    mdd = ((cum - cum.cummax())/cum.cummax()).min()\n",
    "    print(f'  {label}: CAGR={cagr*100:.2f}%, Vol={vol*100:.2f}%, SR={sr:.3f}, MDD={mdd*100:.2f}%')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Moving Average Crossover vs. Buy & Hold:')\n",
    "perf(ret_m,   'Buy & Hold')\n",
    "perf(strat_r, 'MA(50/200)')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(13, 8), sharex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].plot(prices_m.values, color='#4a90d9', lw=1, alpha=0.8, label='Preis')\n",
    "axes[0].plot(ma_50.values,    color='#e67e22', lw=1.5, label='MA 50')\n",
    "axes[0].plot(ma_200.values,   color='#c0392b', lw=2,   label='MA 200')\n",
    "# Highlight: Long-Phasen\n",
    "long_mask = signal_ma == 1\n",
    "axes[0].fill_between(range(T_mom), prices_m.min(), prices_m.max(),\n",
    "                     where=long_mask, alpha=0.1, color='green')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('MA(50/200) Crossover Strategie', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Preis')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].plot(cum_bh.values,    color='#95a5a6', lw=2, label='Buy & Hold')\n",
    "axes[1].plot(cum_strat.values, color='#2ecc71', lw=2, label='MA Strategie (grüne Phasen)')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Kumulativer Wert: Strategie vs. Buy & Hold', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Kumulativer Wert')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('momentum.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
