    "---\n",
    "## 17. Statistical Arbitrage & Pairs Trading mit Kointegration\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theorie\n",
    "\n",
    "**Statistical Arbitrage (StatArb)** nutzt **statistisch vorhersagbare Preisbeziehungen** zwischen Assets aus, ohne auf fundamentale Analysen angewiesen zu sein.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pairs Trading:** Die einfachste Form von StatArb. Idee:\n",
    "1. Finde zwei Assets die sich historisch ähnlich bewegen (z.B. Volkswagen und BMW)\n",
    "2. Wenn der Spread zwischen ihnen zu groß wird: Kaufe das unterbewertete, verkaufe das überbewertete\n",
    "3. Wenn der Spread wieder normal ist: Schließe beide Positionen\n",
    "\n",
    "### Kointegration vs. Korrelation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Wichtiger Unterschied:** Zwei Aktien können hoch korreliert sein (beide steigen), aber nicht kointeriert. Kointegration bedeutet: Es gibt eine **Linearkombination** beider Zeitreihen die **stationär** ist (Mean-Revertend):\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Spread}_t = P_{A,t} - \\beta \\cdot P_{B,t} \\sim \\text{stationär}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Engle-Granger Test (1987):**\n",
    "1. Schätze $\\beta$ via OLS: $P_A = \\alpha + \\beta P_B + \\epsilon$\n",
    "2. Teste ob Residuen $\\epsilon$ stationär sind (ADF-Test)\n",
    "3. Wenn stationär → Kointegration → Spread ist Mean-Reverting → Pairs Trade möglich\n",
    "\n",
    "### Hedging Ratio β\n",
    "\n",
    "Der **Hedging Ratio β** bestimmt wie viele Einheiten von B pro Einheit A gehandelt werden, um den Marktexposure zu neutralisieren. Ein Pairs Trade ist **marktneutral** wenn der Spread unabhängig von der allgemeinen Marktrichtung ist.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quelle:** Engle & Granger (1987); Gatev, E. et al. (2006). *Pairs Trading: Performance of a Relative-Value Arbitrage Rule*. Review of Financial Studies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Kointegrations-Simulation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "T_pair = 756   # 3 Jahre\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gemeinsamer Trend (Random Walk)\n",
    "common_trend = np.cumsum(np.random.normal(0, 0.005, T_pair))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Asset A und B: folgen dem gleichen Trend + idiosynkratisches Rauschen\n",
    "beta_true = 1.5\n",
    "noise_A   = np.cumsum(np.random.normal(0, 0.003, T_pair))  # kleines stationäres Rauschen\n",
    "noise_B   = np.random.normal(0, 0.004, T_pair)              # weißes Rauschen\n",
    "\n",
    "# Spread ist stationär: P_A - beta * P_B = stationärer Prozess\n",
    "price_A = 100 * np.exp(common_trend + 0.3 * simulate_ou(20, 0, 0.03, 0, T_pair/TRADING_DAYS))\n",
    "price_B = 100 * np.exp(common_trend / beta_true + np.cumsum(noise_B))\n",
    "\n",
    "prices_A = pd.Series(price_A)\n",
    "prices_B = pd.Series(price_B)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Schritt 1: Hedging Ratio via OLS ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "beta_hat_p, alpha_hat_p = np.polyfit(prices_B.values, prices_A.values, 1)\n",
    "spread_p = prices_A - beta_hat_p * prices_B - alpha_hat_p\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Schritt 2: ADF-Test auf Stationarität ─────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Vereinfachter ADF: OLS Regression von delta(spread) auf spread(t-1)\n",
    "delta_spread = spread_p.diff().dropna().values\n",
    "spread_lag   = spread_p.shift(1).dropna().values\n",
    "adf_beta, _, _, adf_p, _ = stats.linregress(spread_lag, delta_spread)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Geschätzter Hedging Ratio β  : {beta_hat_p:.4f}  (wahrer Wert: {beta_true:.1f})')\n",
    "print(f'ADF-Koeffizient (γ)          : {adf_beta:.6f}  (negativ = Mean-Reversion)')\n",
    "print(f'ADF p-Wert                   : {adf_p:.6f}')\n",
    "print(f'Kointegration                : {\"JA ✓\" if adf_p < 0.05 else \"NEIN ✗\"}  (p < 0.05)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Schritt 3: Trading Signale ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "spread_mean = spread_p.rolling(60).mean()\n",
    "spread_std  = spread_p.rolling(60).std()\n",
    "z_score     = (spread_p - spread_mean) / spread_std\n",
    "\n",
    "# Long spread wenn z < -1 (spread zu eng), short wenn z > +1\n",
    "signal_pairs = pd.Series(np.where(z_score < -1, 1, np.where(z_score > 1, -1, 0)))\n",
    "signal_pairs = signal_pairs.shift(1).fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Renditen des Spread-Trades\n",
    "ret_A_p   = prices_A.pct_change().fillna(0)\n",
    "ret_B_p   = prices_B.pct_change().fillna(0)\n",
    "strat_ret_p = signal_pairs * (ret_A_p - beta_hat_p * ret_B_p)\n",
    "cum_pairs   = (1 + strat_ret_p).cumprod()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(13, 11))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Preise\n",
    "ax2 = axes[0].twinx()\n",
    "axes[0].plot(prices_A.values, color='#4a90d9', lw=1.5, label='Asset A')\n",
    "ax2.plot(prices_B.values, color='#e67e22', lw=1.5, label='Asset B')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Kointerierte Assets: Gleicher Trend, Mean-Reverting Spread', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Asset A Preis', color='#4a90d9')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('Asset B Preis', color='#e67e22')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Spread und z-Score\n",
    "axes[1].plot(spread_p.values, color='#2c3e50', lw=1.5, label='Spread')\n",
    "axes[1].plot(spread_mean.values, color='grey', lw=1, ls='--', label='Rolling Mean')\n",
    "axes[1].fill_between(range(len(spread_p)), spread_mean - spread_std,\n",
    "                     spread_mean + spread_std, alpha=0.15, color='blue', label='±1σ')\n",
    "long_p  = signal_pairs == 1\n",
    "short_p = signal_pairs == -1\n",
    "axes[1].scatter(np.where(long_p)[0],  spread_p.iloc[long_p].values,  color='green', s=15, zorder=5)\n",
    "axes[1].scatter(np.where(short_p)[0], spread_p.iloc[short_p].values, color='red',   s=15, zorder=5)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Spread (= P_A - β·P_B): Mean-Reverting', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Performance\n",
    "axes[2].plot(cum_pairs.values, color='#2ecc71', lw=2)\n",
    "axes[2].axhline(1, color='grey', ls='--', lw=1)\n",
    "axes[2].set_title('Pairs Trade Kumulativer P&L (marktneutral)', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[2].set_ylabel('Kumulativer Wert')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('pairs_trading.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
