    "---\n",
    "## 19. Walk-Forward Analysis & Out-of-Sample Testing\n",
    "\n",
    "### Theorie\n",
    "\n",
    "**In-Sample (IS) vs. Out-of-Sample (OOS):**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **In-Sample:** Daten die zur Parameterschätzung/Optimierung verwendet wurden. Jede Strategie die auf IS-Daten optimiert wird, passt sich an Rauschen an (**Overfitting**).\n",
    "- **Out-of-Sample:** Daten die *nie* zur Entwicklung der Strategie verwendet wurden. OOS-Performance ist die einzig valide Schätzung echter Strategieperformance.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Walk-Forward Analysis** ist die robusteste Backtesting-Methode:\n",
    "1. Teile Daten in rollende Fenster\n",
    "2. **Training Window:** Optimiere Parameter auf diesem Fenster\n",
    "3. **Test Window:** Wende die optimierten Parameter auf das *nächste* Fenster an (OOS)\n",
    "4. Schiebe Fenster vor und wiederhole\n",
    "\n",
    "Das Ergebnis ist eine vollständige OOS-Performance über den gesamten Datensatz – ohne jemals in die Zukunft zu schauen.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Verhältnis OOS/IS Performance:** Wenn eine Strategie IS eine Sharpe von 2.0 hat, aber OOS nur 0.5, ist das ein starkes Overfitting-Signal. Eine Faustregel: OOS-Performance sollte mindestens 50% der IS-Performance betragen.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quelle:** de Prado (2018), Kap. 11 & 12; Chan (2013), Kap. 3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Walk-Forward Backtest ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "T_wf         = 252 * 7    # 7 Jahre Gesamtdaten\n",
    "train_window = 252         # 1 Jahr Training\n",
    "test_window  = 63          # 3 Monate Test (OOS)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simuliere Preisserie\n",
    "r_wf    = pd.Series(np.random.normal(0.0003, 0.011, T_wf))\n",
    "price_wf = (1 + r_wf).cumprod()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Walk-Forward: In jedem Training-Fenster optimiere die MA-Länge\n",
    "# Teste MA 20, 50, 100 und wähle die beste IS-Sharpe\n",
    "wf_returns_is  = []\n",
    "wf_returns_oos = []\n",
    "best_params    = []\n",
    "\n",
    "t = train_window\n",
    "while t + test_window <= T_wf:\n",
    "    train_r = r_wf.iloc[t-train_window:t]\n",
    "    test_r  = r_wf.iloc[t:t+test_window]\n",
    "    train_p = price_wf.iloc[t-train_window:t]\n",
    "    test_p  = price_wf.iloc[t:t+test_window]\n",
    "\n",
    "    best_sr, best_ma = -np.inf, 20\n",
    "    for ma_len in [10, 20, 30, 50, 100]:\n",
    "        if ma_len >= len(train_p):\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        ma      = train_p.rolling(ma_len).mean()\n",
    "        sig     = (train_p > ma).astype(int).shift(1).fillna(0)\n",
    "        strat_r = sig * train_r\n",
    "        if strat_r.std() > 0:\n",
    "            sr = strat_r.mean() / strat_r.std() * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS)\n",
    "            if sr > best_sr:\n",
    "                best_sr, best_ma = sr, ma_len\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Apply best IS parameter to OOS\n",
    "    # For simplicity: use last signal from training as starting point\n",
    "    ma_oos  = pd.concat([train_p.iloc[-best_ma:], test_p]).rolling(best_ma).mean().iloc[best_ma:]\n",
    "    sig_oos = (test_p.values > ma_oos.values).astype(int)\n",
    "    oos_r   = pd.Series(np.roll(sig_oos, 1) * test_r.values)\n",
    "\n",
    "    wf_returns_is.append(best_sr)\n",
    "    if oos_r.std() > 0:\n",
    "        wf_returns_oos.append(oos_r.mean() / oos_r.std() * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        wf_returns_oos.append(0)\n",
    "    best_params.append(best_ma)\n",
    "    t += test_window\n",
    "\n",
    "is_sr  = np.array(wf_returns_is)\n",
    "oos_sr = np.array(wf_returns_oos)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Walk-Forward Analysis – {len(is_sr)} Fenster:')\n",
    "print(f'  Ø Sharpe IS  (In-Sample)     : {is_sr.mean():.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'  Ø Sharpe OOS (Out-of-Sample) : {oos_sr.mean():.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'  OOS/IS Verhältnis            : {oos_sr.mean()/is_sr.mean():.2f}')\n",
    "print(f'  (Faustregel: OOS > 50% von IS = kein extremes Overfitting)')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].scatter(is_sr, oos_sr, alpha=0.6, color='#4a90d9', s=60)\n",
    "axes[0].axline([0,0], [1,1], color='red', ls='--', lw=1, label='IS=OOS (perfekt)')\n",
    "axes[0].axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.7)\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(0, color='black', lw=0.7)\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('IS Sharpe Ratio')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('OOS Sharpe Ratio')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('IS vs. OOS Sharpe: Walk-Forward', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.arange(len(is_sr))\n",
    "axes[1].bar(x - 0.2, is_sr,  0.35, label='IS Sharpe',  color='#4a90d9', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "axes[1].bar(x + 0.2, oos_sr, 0.35, label='OOS Sharpe', color='#2ecc71', alpha=0.8)\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(0, color='black', lw=0.7)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('IS vs. OOS Sharpe pro Fenster', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Fenster-Nummer')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Sharpe Ratio')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('walk_forward.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
